.SH "NAME"
timed\-process \- Run background process for limited amount of time
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    timed\-process [\-e exit_status] timeout command [<arg> [<arg> ...]]
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This script runs \fIcommand\fR for a specified amount of time and if it
doesn't finish, it kills the process.  If \fIcommand\fR runs and exits
before the given timeout, \fBtimed-process\fR returns the exit value of
\&\fIcommand\fR.  If \fIcommand\fR did not exit before \fItimeout\fR seconds,
then \fBtimed-process\fR will kill the process and returns an exit value
of 255, unless the \-e command line option is set, which instructs
\&\fBtimed-process\fR to return a different exit value.  This allows the
user of \fBtimed-process\fR to determine if the process ended normally or
was killed.
